BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:debug-007-long-title@example.test
DTSTAMP:20260520T100000Z
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Rome:20260607T150000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Rome:20260607T163000
SUMMARY:[TALK] A longer title: parsing should keep punctuation, commas, and colons in the title (Nora Klein, ETH Zurich; Oscar Lee, MIT)
LOCATION:Conference Room
DESCRIPTION:<p>Case 7: title contains punctuation and commas.</p>\n<p>The parser should still detect only the final parenthesized author section.</p>
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:debug-008-empty-author-fragment@example.test
