DTEND;TZID=Europe/Rome:20260110T110000
SUMMARY:[PAST] Past event for ended rendering (Zoe Adams, University of Cambridge)
LOCATION:Old Room
DESCRIPTION:<p>Case 11: past event. Useful if you run the renderer with a date after this event.</p>
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:debug-012-long-abstract@example.test
DTSTAMP:20260520T100000Z
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Rome:20260611T100000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Rome:20260611T113000
SUMMARY:[ABSTRACT] Event with a long abstract (Anna Long, University of Turin; Bruno Text)
LOCATION:Room G
DESCRIPTION:<p>This is a deliberately long abstract used to test truncation in the Pug renderer.</p>\n<p>Line two contains enough text to be split across multiple visual lines in the generated card and should contribute to the line budget.</p>\n<p>Line three continues with more text about the event, the speakers, the topic, and the expected audience.</p>\n<p>Line four is here to make sure the renderer eventually appends an ellipsis or the parenthesized continuation marker when needed.</p>\n<p>Line five should probably not be fully visible depending on the current max_lines and avg_chars settings.</p>
END:VEVENT

END:VCALENDAR
